WHAT IS THE ONLINE SIG?

The Online and Interactive Information Special Interest Group
(or "Online SIG") is an informal group of people who share
an interest in the growing world of electronically-delivered
information.  This includes topics such as online documentation,
user interface design, interactive tutorials, help systems,
information retrieval technologies, and multimedia.

Although the Online SIG is sponsored by the Silicon Valley chapter
of the Society for Technical Communication (STC), you need not
be a member of the STC to attend Online SIG meetings.  There is no
admission fee to attend, nor any refreshments available before, during,
or after the meeting.  The standard SIG meeting occurs the third Tuesday
of each month, at Software Publishing Corporation (SPC) in Santa Clara.
(See the DIRECTIONS section of this message for details.)   Meetings
start at 6:30 PM and end around 8:30.  But we sometimes meet at other
times or other places.


